content: I'm feeling more confident about prioritizing my morning routine, especially now that we've discussed how to establish a consistent wake-up time on weekends, cut down on screen time, stay motivated to exercise, and make reading a habit. I think I'll try to schedule my exercise routine for Saturday and Sunday mornings, followed by some reading time. This way, I can make the most of my weekends and set myself up for a positive and productive week ahead. Do you have any tips on how to meal prep for the week ahead on Sundays?
